is time a commondity will you cash it in or crush it out time appears different to all of us the sleeper has a different concept of time from the person watching over him time moves swiftly for the sleeper slowly for the awakened time moves slowly for those in agony and especially those without a relationship with our god creator the frightened the bored the lonely find ways of speeding the agonizing slowness of time time is painful for those awaiting death or trial th business man never has enough time and tries to buy it with impatience procrastinating to buy time we discover we have less time and we have more to do in that lesser amount of time life is such a paradox do you find that true for you too or have you found god's stillness and bathing in his now as usual there are always many grammar teachers around ya thanks for the correction anyway yes i feel that time is a commodity to me it is like money only much more expensive if you lose money you might be able to get some again but if you lose time by wasting or mis using it you can never get those moments back again recently i have been gathering quotations i like and here are a couple of good ones about time nothing is as far away as one minute ago jim bishop regret for wasted time is more wasted time mason cooley o magazine april yes i enjoy god's stillness although i often get out of that place and into busy ness instead it is a real discpline to stay in that place of quietness and rest be still and know that i am god psalm first part let us labour therefore to enter into that rest lest any man fall after the same example of unbelief hebrews he that dwelleth in the secret place of the most high shall abide under the shadow of the almighty psalm God Eastern Orthodox Church Jiddu Krishnamurti EastEnders Socrates Shaggy dog story Heaven Procrastination H. G. Wells The Amazing Race Prostate cancer Duties of the Heart Names of God in Judaism God Emperor of Dune Poker jargon Similarities between the Bible and th